I'd like to create a dashboard to visualize our monthly sales performance using data from our GreptimeDB database. Please run the following SQL query on the greptimedb-mcp-server to get the sales data for the last 12 months:

SELECT MONTH(sale_date) AS month, YEAR(sale_date) AS year, SUM(sales_amount) AS total_sales FROM sales WHERE sale_date >= DATE_SUB(CURDATE(), INTERVAL 12 MONTH) GROUP BY year, month ORDER BY year, month;

Once you have the results, please save them as a CSV file named 'monthly_sales_last_12_months.csv'. Then, load this file into the Vizro MCP server for analysis using its file path or URL. After loading, please provide the resulting data_infos array from the analysis step.

Next, validate a Vizro dashboard configuration that displays total sales per month as a bar chart, using the following config object and the data_infos array:
{
  "charts": [{
    "type": "bar",
    "x": "month",
    "y": "total_sales",
    "title": "Total Sales per Month (Last 12 Months)"
  }],
  "data_source": "monthly_sales_last_12_months.csv"
}
Set auto_open to false.

Finally, validate the chart code using the same config and the appropriate data_info (from the data_infos array), with auto_open set to false, to ensure the chart code is correct and ready for use.
